## Implementation Plan

### 1. Extend `BindingVmServiceFake` to serve the fixture for `core.get_stable_observation`

File: `packages/exploration_agent/test/_support/binding_vm_service_fake.dart`

Add the `ObservationFixture` import and a constant for the intercepted method. Add a named optional constructor parameter. In `callServiceExtension`, when the method is `core.get_stable_observation` AND a fixture is configured, short-circuit to the fixture body wrapped in the binding's envelope (`{type: 'Observation', value: <body>}`) without touching `_binding.invokeServiceExtension`.

```dart
import 'package:exploration_agent/src/dogfood/observation_fixture.dart';

class BindingVmServiceFake extends VmService {
  BindingVmServiceFake(this._binding, {this.observationFixture})
      : super(const Stream<dynamic>.empty(), (_) {});

  final ExplorationBinding _binding;

  /// Optional canned observation. When non-null, calls to
  /// `ext.flutter.exploration.core.get_stable_observation` return
  /// `{type: 'Observation', value: observationFixture.body}` instead
  /// of executing the binding's real handler. Other extensions and
  /// plugin tools route normally regardless. (lenny-cx6.48)
  final ObservationFixture? observationFixture;

  static const String _kObservationMethod =
      'ext.flutter.exploration.core.get_stable_observation';

  @override
  Future<Response> callServiceExtension(
    String method, {
    String? isolateId,
    Map<String, dynamic>? args,
  }) async {
    // Fixture-serving short-circuit (lenny-cx6.48). When a fixture is
    // configured, the binding's empty-tree observation is bypassed for
    // exactly this one method; everything else falls through to the
    // registry/extension routing below.
    final ObservationFixture? fx = observationFixture;
    if (fx != null && method == _kObservationMethod) {
      final Response r = Response();
      r.json = <String, dynamic>{
        'type': 'Observation',
        'value': fx.body,
      };
      return r;
    }
    // ...existing arg conversion and routing unchanged...
  }
}
```

Keep the rest of `callServiceExtension` byte-identical to today (arg coercion, prefix check, mergedTools lookup, `invokePluginTool` vs `invokeServiceExtension`). Only the new short-circuit branch is added.

Also update the file-level dartdoc to note the optional fixture-serving behavior and that it is the lenny-cx6.48 seam for canned observations.

