description:
## Problem

`BindingVmServiceFake.callServiceExtension` (the in-process VM-service fake shared by cvl.4, cx6.41, and cx6.43 — see `packages/exploration_agent/test/_support/binding_vm_service_fake.dart`) routes calls by URL prefix:

```dart
const String corePrefix = 'ext.flutter.exploration.core.';
const String pluginPrefix = 'ext.flutter.exploration.';
if (method.startsWith(corePrefix)) {
  body = await _binding.invokeServiceExtension(method, stringArgs);
} else if (method.startsWith(pluginPrefix)) {
  body = await _binding.invokePluginTool(method, stringArgs);
} else {
  throw RPCError(...);
}
```

This is **wrong for all `core.*` tool methods** and has always been. `invokeServiceExtension` only dispatches `ExplorationBinding._extensionCallbacks` — which the binding populates with handshake, `get_stable_observation`, `get_recent_errors`, `screenshot`, `diagnostics_warnings`. The `core.tap`/`core.done`/`core.fill`/... per-tool extensions are registered by `CorePlugin.initialize()` via `developer.registerExtension` and never enter `_extensionCallbacks`. So:

- Pre-cx6.45 (real CorePlugin running): `core.tap` → fake routes to `invokeServiceExtension` → no extension callback found → throws → agent sees `VmServiceConnectionLost`.
- Post-cx6.45 (CorePlugin opted out, `_StandInPlugin('core', ...)` registered in pluginRegistry): `core.tap` → fake STILL routes to `invokeServiceExtension` (not the stand-in via `invokePluginTool`) → no extension callback → throws → `connectionLost` again.

The bug has been latent since cvl.4 because no test exercised a `core.*` tool through this fake. cx6.43's harness now does, and cx6.45's stand-in fix was supposed to make `core.tap` work — it didn't, because the fake never reaches the stand-in.

## Confirmed run (msg_8F0727EF071, qwen3.6-moe, 12s)

Post-cx6.45 dogfood harness run with `--model qwen3.6-moe`:

- swift-infer returned `tool_calls=[{name:"core_tap", arguments:{x:"0.1", y:"0.1"}}]`.
- Agent decoded → `core.tap`, called `VmServiceClient.executeAction("core.tap", ...)`.
- Fake routed `ext.flutter.exploration.core.tap` → `invokeServiceExtension` → no callback → exception → agent surfaces `HarnessError.connectionLost`.
- Footer now correctly captures `harness_error: connection_lost` (thanks to cx6.45) — diagnostic is clean, but the underlying routing is still broken.

## Steps to Reproduce

1. Check out HEAD (post-cx6.45).
2. Run any test that constructs `BindingVmServiceFake` (or its inline `_BindingVmServiceFake` clones) against an `ExplorationBinding` whose `core` namespace tools are registered via the real `CorePlugin` (i.e. `optOutDefaultPlugins` is false). The cleanest reproducer is to drive `fake.callServiceExtension('ext.flutter.exploration.core.tap', args: {'x': 0.1, 'y': 0.1})`.
3. Observe: the call throws because `_extensionCallbacks` has no entry for `ext.flutter.exploration.core.tap` — that extension was registered by `CorePlugin.initialize` via `developer.registerExtension`, never via `ExplorationBinding.registerExtensionCallback`, so `invokeServiceExtension` cannot find it.
4. Expected: the call reaches `CorePlugin`'s `TapTool` and returns a `{ok: true, ...}` envelope.

Reproduces 100% of the time; the dogfood run cited above is one externally-observable instance of this same failure mode.

## Fix

Replace the prefix-based heuristic with a registry lookup. The fake has access to `_binding`, so it can ask: "is this method a registered plugin tool?"

```dart
@override
Future<Response> callServiceExtension(
  String method, {
  String? isolateId,
  Map<String, dynamic>? args,
}) async {
  final Map<String, String> stringArgs = ...;
  // Tools registered via PluginContext.registerExtension live in the
  // plugin registry's merged-tools map (keyed by '<ns>.<tool>'). The
  // binding-owned extensions (handshake, get_stable_observation,
  // get_recent_errors, screenshot, diagnostics_warnings) live in
  // _extensionCallbacks and are reached via invokeServiceExtension.
  const String prefix = 'ext.flutter.exploration.';
  if (!method.startsWith(prefix)) {
    throw RPCError(method, -32601, 'Unknown method "$method"');
  }
  final String suffix = method.substring(prefix.length); // '<ns>.<tool>'
  if (_binding.pluginRegistry.mergedTools().containsKey(suffix)) {
    body = await _binding.invokePluginTool(method, stringArgs);
  } else {
    body = await _binding.invokeServiceExtension(method, stringArgs);
  }
  ...
}
```

This works because:
- Plugin tools (incl. `_StandInPlugin('core', ...)` post-cx6.45 AND real `CorePlugin` tools when present) all populate `pluginRegistry.mergedTools()` keyed by `<ns>.<tool>`.
- Binding-owned extensions (handshake etc.) are NOT in `mergedTools()` and fall through to `invokeServiceExtension`.
- No prefix-based assumption; the registry is the source of truth.

## Out of scope

- Hoisting the fake into a shared `test_support/` location (lenny-imr).
- The `pluginRegistry` accessor on `ExplorationBinding` — if it's not already public-enough for the fake, expose a `@visibleForTesting` getter rather than reaching into private state.
- Per-turn verbose logging in the harness (still open, sibling concern).

## Anchors

- `packages/exploration_agent/test/_support/binding_vm_service_fake.dart` (the broken routing)
- `packages/exploration_flutter/lib/src/binding/exploration_binding.dart` — `invokeServiceExtension`, `invokePluginTool`, `_extensionCallbacks`, `pluginRegistry`.
- `packages/exploration_flutter/lib/src/contract/registry.dart` — `PluginRegistry.mergedTools()`.
- All four call sites of `BindingVmServiceFake` (cvl.4, cx6.41 has its own inline copy, cx6.43 imports the shared one twice) — the fix must propagate.
- Hoist sibling `lenny-imr` is still open; this fix should be made in the canonical copy and mirrored to cvl.4 / cx6.41 by hand until imr lands.

## Diagnosed via

Dogfood run `/tmp/lenny-dogfood/run6.jsonl` against live swift-infer with the MoE model post-cx6.45. The harness now correctly surfaces `harness_error: connection_lost` in the footer, but inspection of the fake's routing showed `core.tap` is being dispatched to the wrong helper.

