   - Update the harness's `finally` to actually do the right thing: capture the original `capturedException` before any further work, attempt `session.end()` (already best-effort), then `trace.writeFooter` in its own try:
   ```dart
   } finally {
     try {
       await session.end();
     } catch (_) { /* best-effort, keep contract */ }
     String? recoveryError;
     try {
       await trace.writeFooter(
         outcome: outcome.name,
         exception: capturedException?.toString(),
       );
     } catch (e) {
       // Defensive: a secondary error during footer-write must not
       // mask the original. Attempt a degraded retry that carries
       // both.
       recoveryError = e.toString();
       try {
         await trace.writeFooter(
           outcome: outcome.name,
           exception: capturedException?.toString(),
           recoveryError: recoveryError,
         );
       } catch (_) { /* nothing more we can do */ }
     }
   }
   ```
