## Wire source
swift-infer (and anthropic, post-cx6.49) emit the request id on the SSE 'message_start' event as message.message.id (e.g. 'msg_5C16E942855'). Confirmed against /v1/trace/msg_5C16E942855 — that id is the trace key. No X-Request-Id response header; SSE payload is the only carrier.

## Field name
'provider_request_id' on the wire (in the dogfood_turn.decision map) and 'providerRequestId' in Dart. Generic across providers — Anthropic's wire emits the same shape, and OpenAI's chat.completion id (if/when added) fits the same slot. The reader still pastes the value into swift-infer's /v1/trace/:id when the provider is swift-infer; the name doesn't change ergonomics.

## Plumbing (high level)
1. Add 'providerRequestId: String?' to ModelDecision (packages/exploration_agent/lib/src/provider/types.dart:72).
2. swift_infer_provider.dart and anthropic_provider.dart: in the SSE loop, capture evt['message']['id'] when type == 'message_start'; set on the returned ModelDecision. Null when absent (defensive — never assume the event arrived).
3. TurnRecord (packages/exploration_agent/lib/src/trajectory/records.dart): add 'providerRequestId: String?'. LoopDriver passes it from ModelDecision into the TurnRecord at the same site it populates proposedAction.
4. AgentDogfoodHarness _DogfoodInterceptingTrajectoryWriter.writeTurn (agent_dogfood_harness.dart:453): read t.providerRequestId, add 'provider_request_id' to the decision map when non-null.

## Out of scope
- OpenAI provider — different wire (chat.completion not SSE message_start); separate bead if wanted.
- Backfilling old runs — net-new from this point.
- Surfacing the id in TrajectoryWriter's canonical TurnRecord JSON (only the dogfood writer needs it; canonical writer can ignore the field). NOTE: For schema stability the canonical writer DOES serialize the field (so reader round-trip stays lossless), but downstream UIs that don't read it are unaffected.
