## Decisions resolved during specify

- **Writer (Q1)**: a panel-local `BroadcastTrajectorySink` (in-memory) backs the live `TrajectoryWriter` and doubles as the source for the timeline tab. `DtdTrajectorySink` (already in this package) is the disk-persisting successor; a comment in the controller points at it. No `TrajectoryWriter.noop()` is introduced — a real writer is required so the manual AC ("trajectory appears in the timeline tab") is observable end-to-end.
- **Tool descriptors (Q2)**: reuse the existing `ext.flutter.exploration.handshake` plugin manifest already surfaced via `ManifestProbeResult`/`session.handshake`. Lift `buildPluginTools` from `exploration_cli` (pure Dart) into `exploration_agent` so both frontends share one code path. No new VM-service extension; no handshake-contract change. `coreTools: const <ToolDescriptor>[]` (matches CLI today); the binding-side `ActionValidator` (cx6.17) is the authoritative arg check; full schemas are cx6.39's job.
- **Caching (Q3)**: build the merged map once per `session.run`, from `session.handshake.plugins` captured at start(). `DefaultLoopHost.activePluginNamespaces()` still re-evaluates per turn against `_disabled`, preserving the PRD §16 dynamic-merge contract within a run. A reconnect (new session) → fresh map.

