### 2. Extract `_wirePlugins` — `packages/exploration_flutter/lib/src/binding/exploration_binding.dart`

Add field `final List<Future<void> Function()> _teardowns = <Future<void> Function()>[];` and method:

```dart
/// Caller must already have set `_instance = this`.
void _wirePlugins(List<ExplorationPlugin> plugins) {
  _sessionClock = Stopwatch()..start();
  _errors = ErrorRingBuffer(capacity: _errorBufferCapacity, sessionClock: _sessionClock);
  _pluginRegistry = PluginRegistry(scheduler: this);
  _corePlugin = CorePlugin(semantics: _semanticsCapture);
  _pluginRegistry.register(_corePlugin);
  for (final p in plugins) {
    try { _pluginRegistry.register(p); }
    on StateError catch (e) { debugPrint('[exploration] skipping plugin ${p.namespace}: $e'); }
    on ArgumentError catch (e) { debugPrint('[exploration] skipping plugin ${p.namespace}: $e'); }
  }
  _installErrorHooks();
  _registerCoreExtensions();
  _registerDiagnosticsExtension();
  scheduleMicrotask(() => _pluginRegistry.initializeAll());
}
```

In `ensureInitialized`, after `_instance = binding;` (current line ~184), replace the inlined wiring at current lines 154-190 with `binding._wirePlugins(binding._plugins);`. Constructor still receives `_plugins` for the legacy `plugins` getter — keep field/ctor unchanged.

