## Approach

Original spec required exporting top-level `PromptPayload(messages, tools)` and `ToolDefinition(name, description, parametersSchema)`. cx6.14 already shipped `PromptPayload(systemMessage, userMessages, tools: List<ToolDescriptor>)` and `ToolDescriptor(name, description, inputSchema)` at `packages/exploration_agent/lib/src/provider/types.dart`. Adding the `.13` versions causes `ambiguous_export`.

**Resolution: reuse `.14`'s shipped types.** `.13` does not introduce new payload types — it introduces the **memory artifacts** (`RunningSummary`, `ActionRing`, `TokenCounter`) and the **assembler** (`PromptAssembler`) that produces a `PromptPayload` from those artifacts plus the merged tool list. The assembler outputs the existing `PromptPayload` shape; the system message contains AGENTS.md + goal + summary + recent actions; the user messages contain the serialized observation + diff; the tools list is the merged list passed through unchanged.

This keeps the `.14`/`.13` boundary clean: `.14` owns provider value types; `.13` owns memory + prompt construction.

## Constraints

- Web-compatible (PRD §22): no `dart:io`. AGENTS.md is loaded as a string by callers — assembler does not read filesystem. (cx6.20 CLI handles file I/O when wiring the harness.)
- Pure assembler — same inputs yield structurally equal output (no time, no I/O, no caching).
- `ToolDescriptor.inputSchema` is `Map<String, dynamic>` (raw draft-07). Tools list passes through unchanged so cx6.14's `ActionSchema` composer can consume it directly.

