## Approach
Connect-time host diagnostic that walks the widget tree to identify common interactable widgets lacking semantics annotations: bare `GestureDetector` (no enclosing `Semantics`/button-like ancestor), `InkWell`/`InkResponse` without semantic labels, and any user-flagged custom-button class via a configurable list. Surface results via `ext.flutter.exploration.core.diagnostics_warnings`. Diagnostic message points users at the plugin authoring guide (cx6.35) as the canonical fix path.

## Constraints
- Connect-time diagnostic ONLY; not a per-turn observation contributor.
- Must NOT crash the session if the walk fails — degrade with a log line.
- P3 by design — v0.5 demoted host-side custom-widget handling to a plugin concern.
- `kDebugMode || kProfileMode` gating (PRD §6.1).

## Ruled out
- v0.2 `isInteractiveWidget` host config knob (v0.5 explicitly OUT).
- Auto-fix / auto-annotation (invasive, brittle).
- Per-turn re-runs (interactable surface doesn't change meaningfully turn-to-turn).

